0.description:
Let's get ready for the party.
First grab the 4 words that best describe you.

choices.text: practical
grounded
realistic
rational
scientific
intellectual
free-spirited
artsy
independent
helpful
friendly
trustworthy
energetic
ambitious
sociable
orderly
business-like
efficient

1.description: On the way out the door you see that your favorite TV show is on. The host asked you to arrive precisely at 7:00pm. You decide to:

choices.text: Skip the show, it's important for you to be punctual.
Figure it's ok to be a few minutes late and split the difference.
Watch the end of the show and then hurry over.
You're not worried about arriving late, at this point your friends expect it.

2.description: On your way to the party do you stop at the store to pick up a gift?

choices.text: No
Yes, you easily remember your friend's favorite snack and bring that.
You, you pick up something nice that you think others will enjoy.
Yes, you pick up something inexpensive and convenient.

3.description: You've arrived at the party, where to?

choices.text: Mysterious Strangers
Old Friend
Balcony
Food
Mysterious foreign food
Something unusual made by the host
Maybe a spicy dip
Comfort food

4-mystery.description: One of the strangers is a friend of the host named Samantha. She reveals that she is a ventriloquist from Las Vegas. You are:

choices.text: Fascinated and excited to ask lots of questions.
Intrigued, you like meeting people with unusual careers.
Intrigued, but you figure you don’t have much in common with Samantha.
Wishing you could talk to someone you relate to more.

4-friend.description: As you are talking another party guest, named Samantha, comes in to join the conversation. She reveals that she is a ventriloquist from Las Vegas. You are:

choices.text: Fascinated and excited to ask lots of questions.
Intrigued, you like meeting people with unusual careers.
Intrigued, but you figure you don’t have much in common with Samantha.
Wishing you could talk to someone you relate to more.

4-balcony.description: After taking in the view you return to the party and meet another guest, named Samantha. She reveals that she is a ventriloquist from Las Vegas. You are:

choices.text: Fascinated and excited to ask lots of questions.
Intrigued, you like meeting people with unusual careers.
Intrigued, but you figure you don’t have much in common with Samantha.
Wishing you could talk to someone you relate to more.

4-food.description: While eating you meet another party guest, named Samantha. She reveals that she is a ventriloquist from Las Vegas. You are:

choices.text: Fascinated and excited to ask lots of questions.
Intrigued, you like meeting people with unusual careers.
Intrigued, but you figure you don’t have much in common with Samantha.
Wishing you could talk to someone you relate to more.

5.description: Samantha says: "I hate how competitive show business is, I much prefer working cooperatively with people." You reply:

choices.text: "I agree. I would hate the competition too."
"Learning to compete is important but sometimes it goes too far."
"I usually like competition it is a good way to challenge myself."
"I love to be competitive. It makes things more interesting."

6.description: Samantha says: "I also have a hard time staying organized. Sometimes, I just miss appointments completely because I can’t keep track." You think you yourself:

choices.text: Wow, I would never miss appointments like that.
Sticking to a schedule is hard but it’s also important to be reliable.
I can relate, I sometimes miss appointments and deadlines too.
That’s not a big deal, it’s more important to enjoy life than to be organized.

food-2.description: You and Samantha decide to grab a snack. You choose:

choices.text: Mysterious foreign food
Something unusual made by the host
Maybe a spicy dip
Comfort food

7.description:
Samantha asks: "So, if you could have a job that fit who you are best what would it be like?"
I am the kind of person who is:

choices.text: practical & direct
curious & analytical
creative & intuitive
friendly & helpful
ambitious & energetic
well-organized & efficient
work with my hands
explore ideas
express myself creatively
teach others
lead others
organize information

9-notie.description: ...So maybe a good fit would be something like a:

choices.text: mechanic or electrician
scientist or engineer
artist or designer
teacher or nurse
salesperson or executive
accountant or clerk

9-tie.description: ...So maybe a good fit would be something like a:

choices.text: mechanic or electrician
scientist or engineer
artist or designer
teacher or nurse
salesperson or executive
accountant or clerk

10.description:
As you are talking you find that several new people have joined the conversation and you've built up quite the audience.

You are:

choices.text: In your element.
Pleased to have new people to talk to.
Nervous about the crowd.
Looking for excuses to get out of the center of attention.

11.description:
Ooooops! You lean back and knock over a glass of wine.

You:

choices.text: Feel terrible and anxious about how mad the host will be. You almost don't want to tell them.
Think to yourself "why does this kind of thing always happen to me?"
Feel bad but figure these things happen.
Are totally calm, what's a party without a little spilled wine anyway?

12.description: You excuse yourself to clean up the wine. While cleaning you overhear someone talking about how your co-worker saved the day at work. This makes you:

choices.text: Feel bad about yourself, you know you’ll never measure up.
Feel disappointed it wasn’t you.
Feel pretty neutral.
Glad. People must be talking about you this way too sometimes.

13.description: After cleaning up the wine, you find that the conversation has turned to a colorful debate about different religious prectices. You:

choices.text: Jump right in! You love hearing about people who are different from you.
Are intrigued and go over to listen.
Don't care much for such topics but figure it's interesting enough to join in.
Would rather stay out of it, controversial topics are not for you.

14.description: Someone says: "The way I see it, no one is looking out for me or my beliefs. I have to take care of myself so that I don’t get taken advantage of." you think yourself:

choices.text: How cynical! surely people are more good natured than that.
This person must just be blowing off steam.
You can relate to this, you often think the same thing.
You agree. Anyone who doesn’t think that way is just being naive.

15.description:
Suddenly your phone rings and you have to take it. You duck into the back bedroom to take the call.

Seeing the state of the room you think:

choices.text: Wow. What a mess, my bedroom would never look like this.
Must have been a busy week, no time for cleaning up.
This is probably what your room would look like as well.
Looks pretty neat to me.

16.description: While on the phone you get some bad news. You are:

choices.text: Very worried and anxious. Bad news effects you strongly.
Pretty concerned and look for a friend to help you.
Somewhat concerned but ready to head back to the party.
Disappointed but if you can’t control it there’s no need to get worked up.

17.description:
You head back to the party and hang out some more.
Then it's time to leave, so you thank the host and say good bye.

18.description: After socializing at the party, you find that you are:

choices.text: Energized and ready for the after party.
Feeling great about meeting new friends.
Pleased but also ready to rest.
Quite drained and looking forward to going home and resting.

19.description: On your way home you feel:

choices.text: Happy to have met so many new people.
Ready to be by yourself to recharge.
Excited to have heard new ideas from unusual people.
Glad you didn’t get roped in to any controversial topics.
Pleased that you were a conscientious guest.
Carefree and ready to do the next fun thing.
Pleased that the other people at the party seemed to like you.
Disappointed that you didn’t get into more debates.
Worried that you made a bad impression by spilling the wine.
Calm and relaxed.
